        <name xml:lang="en">ethylene oxide</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
44.05316g/mol is the molar mass of ethylene oxide (C2H4O). 
204.2664g/mol is the molar mass of butyldiglycol acetate (C10H20O4). 

Butyldiglycol acetate is the product of the reaction of ethylene oxide and 1-butanol, which results in diethylene glycol butyl ether, to which acetic acid is added to react and form butyldiglycol acetate.
Chemical reaction:
2C2H4O + CH3(CH2)3OH -&gt; C8H18O3
C8H18O3 + CH3COOH -&gt; C10H2O4 + H2O</comment>
